git repository is a workspace which tracks and manages file with in a folder.
any time when we to use git with a project app, we need to create  a new git repository
we have have as many repos on our machine as needed with separate histories and contents

HEAd is simply a pointer that referes to the current location in the repository.
it points to a particular branch reference
so HEAD always points to the latest commit that made on the master branch, but soon
we can move around and HEAD will change.


git branch :
to view existing branches. The default branch in every git repo is master, though it can be configured.

create a new branch
git branch branch_name

this command will make a new branch based upon the current HEAD
this just creates the branch, it does not switch the new branch that was created,
so HEAD stays the same.


switching to other branch:
git switch branch_name
or 
git checkout branch_name


creating a branch and switiching
git switch  -c branch_name

adding and commiting the files
git commit -a -m "message"

delete a branch
git branch -D branch_name


